I can't agree with the statement that Carters always run small. My son is 95th percentile for height but average weight so he's long and skinny. Lengthwise, he often outgrows the footie bottoms, but on something like this that doesn't have feet, he can wear it past the recommended age. At 8 months, he can still wear a couple of his 3-6 items. Just as with adult clothing, parents really just need to consider their own child's size and shape rather than assuming any clothing will fit every child the same way. For the most part, I have found that, for my son, Carters sizes are right on target.

I believe this game will be better than Mario Party 8. I played Mario Party 4, 5, 6, and 7 and they were all very fun and got more fun with each new addition. Mario Party 8 did have some mistakes. The minigames lost their old-fashioned touch from all the other Mario Partys, and the look was actually not as good the gamecube mario partys (4, 5, 6 and 7). Mario Party 8 was too wii sportsish, as in it was too wii game like. Mario Party 9 looks much better quality and the trailer and pics have sold me more than they did with 8. Also, Mario Party 9 said they are changing up gameplay with a special car for each board to move, instead of your character just moving independently. This means they are addressing the problem of the dullness of Mario Party 8 (or the other Mario Partys too) and making the game more fun. I hope this will make you change your decision.
